public policy,\" Title 54, Chapter 198; \u201cAssembling of negroes. Trading by free negroes,\u201d Section 31; in The Code of Virginia</i></a>. Richmond: William F. Ritchie. 1849. p.&#160;747<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">10 February</span> 2017</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=%E2%80%9COffences+against+public+policy%2C%22+Title+54%2C+Chapter+198%3B+%E2%80%9CAssembling+of+negroes.+Trading+by+free+negroes%2C%E2%80%9D+Section+31%3B+in+The+Code+of+Virginia&amp;rft.place=Richmond&amp;rft.pages=747&amp;rft.pub=William+F.+Ritchie&amp;rft.date=1849&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3Dp1BRAAAAYAAJ%26pg%3DPA747%26lpg%3DPA747&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAnti-literacy+laws+in+the+United+States\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-10\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-10\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">North Carolina Digital History, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"http://www.learnnc.org/lp/editions/nchist-newnation/4384\">http://www.learnnc.org/lp/editions/nchist-newnation/4384</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-11\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-11\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Heather Andrea Williams, <a href=\"/wiki/Self-Taught:_African_American_Education_in_Slavery_and_Freedom\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Self-Taught: African American Education in Slavery and Freedom\">Self-Taught: African American Education in Slavery and Freedom</a>, Univ of North Carolina Press, Nov 20, 2009, p. 17</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-12\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-12\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Robert W.Tabscott John Berry Meachum Defied The Law to Educate Blacks, St. Louis Beacon, Augus